One police officer is missing after an attack by suspected al Shabaab militants in Dabacity, Mandera county last night. Two police vehicles were burnt during the attack. The vehicles were carrying 12 officers who were escorting a bus to Mandera when they were hit by rocket-propelled grenades. "We have communicated with the missing officer. We believe he is in a hide-out in the area," a police officer who sought anonymity said. Another officer was injured during the ambush. A gun is also missing and it is believed to have been taken by the militants. No passenger in the bus was affected as it had passed the scene of the attack. Read: Seven police officers killed in Lamu al Shabaab blast Also read: Teacher recalls how he survived Mandera al Shabaab attack